about it.<br>
<br>
For players actually selling stuff, the bazaar isn't so friendly. You must be logged in to sell stuff (Biggest problem), and if your connection goes wonky, you're booted from the game, which means you won't sell anything.<br>
<br>
I guess the devs took the easy route when designing the bazaar in EQ, because while some of it's features are awesome (item searches with filters!), you can't <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>play</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> the game while you're trying to sell stuff. Um, hello?<br>
<br>
<br>
So here's my suggestion: Revamp the bazaar; specifically the way traders work. There is no reason why players should have to sit online in the bazaar in order to sell stuff. In fact, there are probably a bunch of better ways to do it, but here's what I'd do:<br>
<br>
I'd add a new NPC to the Bazaar called the &quot;Bazaar Baron&quot;. The Baron would act very much like a bank, in that you would store the items you want to sell with him (8 slots), and he would &quot;hire&quot; (spawn) an NPC vendor which would sell your goods in the stalls currently used by player traders. <br>
<br>
The only setback to this would be that the Bazaar Baron would charge you for selling your items; something like 5 or 10% of your selling prices. So if you sell an item for 100pp, you'd get 90pp and the Baron would get 10pp.<br>
<br>
So how would this system be an improvement over the current Bazaar?<br>
<br>
1. You could <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>play</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> the game while your NPC trader sells your items. This would have an added benefit of being able to sell items 24/7 (while servers are up), instead of only when you're not playing.<br>
<br>
2. You wouldn't have to have a character dedicated as a trader mule (free up a character slot).<br>
<br>
3. It'd cut down on SOE's monthly bandwidth costs, which in the end could reduce our monthly subscription fees, or use that money to fund further development.<br>
<br>
4. It'd be a low-profile money sink on the game, which could promote a healthier economy.<br>
<br>
Seriously, I've played SWG and the Bazaar system worked similarly to the one I described above. It blew the EQ's system away, and in fact is probably the best bazaar system in MMOs currently. <br>
I'd like to see something similar to it added to EQ, because it's much more fun to be able to play, and let the game systems sell items for you. <br>
<br>
