These seem to contradict themselves.  My impression after seeing how stacked up people get already that having fixed sell points would reduce the total number of available spots to sell.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>3) intra-zone port to a trader after you found one in the search window, click and it ports you in front of that trader, save time, save rendering, less graphics<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
On my slow computer (the old 1-box, now 2-box), the most lag I get is when I force the greatest amount of new rendering.  You can do this ad hoc by spinning in one place and having to draw all new people and a new background/horizon.  This is essentially what #3 is suggesting.  I do agree, however, the overall lag by cutting out travel lag would be less.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>4) kill all the casino people <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
well DUH!<br>
<br>
<br>
Fredre <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hibashira>Hibashira</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 493<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/26/03 4:58 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>These seem to contradict themselves. My impression after seeing how stacked up people get already that having fixed sell points would reduce the total number of available spots to sell.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
What I mean is the zone should allow more than 500 traders.  That's a hard cap right now.  Fixed sell points would not contradict that if there are as many sell points as the cap.  Right now, the stalls are too deep and traders often layer themselves near the edges and corners.  If, say, each stalls is shallower and each has, 8 or 10 sell points in a grid (thus accomodating 8 to 10 sellers), then the whole zone will be more &quot;neat&quot; and we don't have to jump through hoops to get to the back ones.<br>
<br>
Just a thought.<br>
