<br>
People come into the bazaar for various reasons, but cutting out all the trader's active lines would cut people's reason to be in there.  As initially stated, people would leave the area to play, not hang out afk while selling.  The server wouldn't need to transmit all that information every 6 sec.  They'd just store it.<br>
<br>
If you wanted to really increase traffic, add a feature to enable you to check on your trader while you're playing in another zone.  Or even better, a pop up to inform you if a particular item comes up at a particular price.  Ok, I'm going over the top now. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lunaltoadsnatcher>Lunal Toadsnatcher</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1584<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/26/03 5:15 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> Reading this thread, the cynic in me wonders if the bazaar concept didn't have the ulterior motive of enticing many people to buy second accounts.  Could it be all about the Benjamins? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zertez>zertez</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 192<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/26/03 5:47 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1>  Not sure if someone has already mentioned this but SOE would be pretty stupid to implement this. While I think the idea is good and would help the players out a lot, many have mules or an account just for trading, implementing this would cut into profits somewhat. Maybe I am wrong but personally I know a few who are reluctant to get rid of a 3rd account because they use them to sell exclusively.<br>
