<br>
The best implimentation of this idea is the one where a fixed number of npc vendors sell players items I think.<br>
<br>
However 2 things are obviously not understood here.<br>
<br>
1) I think having actual players act as vendors was supposed to add flavor and variety to the concept as the people standing in stalls would be the same varied players you saw in normal everyday play. Of course alts with names like kmrt totally defeat this purpose...<br>
<br>
2) The items offered in the bazaar as many and varied as they are at any given time represent a fraction of the salable items on the market.  Implimenting this would allow all possible items to enter the marketplace at once within a searchable format.  If you don't see why this is a bad thing consider the price drop when the bazaar first came out. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pickkpockket999>Pickk Pockket999</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 182<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/26/03 6:23 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: This Idea</span><hr size=1> They will never do this as they would lose the revenue from the many &quot;trader&quot; accounts people have purchased. I know quite a few people with a second account used just for bazaar trades.<br>
<br>
Throw in bandwidth utilization and I don't see why they would do this. Every single person who plays the game would have their Bazaar Baron active. That is ~ 1-5k traders constantly active. That equates to quite a large database of items used just for the bazaar. It would end up costing Sony more money to run the game without any potential upside financially. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=27101.topic&start=21&stop=33>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=27101.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=27101.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=27101.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.threadControl?topicID=27101.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=27101.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=27101.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification